  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">MITIGATING THE NEGATIVE EFFECTS OF THE COVID-19 PANDEMIC ON WOMEN IN KAILAHUN</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">- To mitigate the adverse effects on COVID-19 on vulnerable households 
- Contribute to contain the COVID-19 Pandemic in Kailahun District.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Activity 1: Train faith and community leaders on Covid-19 prevention and control, focussing on their roles and responsibilities from across 20 communities: At the district level in Kailahun, SEND will organize a day&apos;s training for faith leaders on Covid-19 prevention and control, focussing on their roles and responsibilities. The faith leaders will come from each of the 20 communities targeted by this action. This training will equip 60 faith leaders with the skills and tools to conduct the awareness-raising activities in the 20 communities targeted on COVID-19. The training cost items include transport refunds, accommodation and diner, feeding, hall rental, and stationary. 

Activity 2: Community awareness raising working with community-based faith leaders (community engagement and radio) and face masks. This activity will target 20 communities in Kailahun district with COVID-19 sensitization messages prepared by the DICOVERC to raise the awareness of men and women on prevention and containment measures to protect themselves. In each of the selected 20 communities, 300 people, including persons with disabilities, will be reached with the sensitization messages. The 300 people targeted in every neighborhood will each get a facem</narrative>
  </description>
